37 SUMMARY
3388 This amendment replaces the bill and changes the title. The amendment establishes a
3399 per diem amount to be paid to the Maine Veterans' Homes facilities for each MaineCare
4400 member, in addition to the regular reimbursement for a MaineCare member in a nursing
4411 facility or residential care facility. The per diem must be adjusted for inflation to the same
Page 3 - 132LR0305(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 115, L.D. 182
412 extent that nursing facilities and residential care facilities are adjusted. Upon
423 implementation of the rate calculation process established by this legislation, any
434 supplemental payments appropriated for the Maine Veterans' Homes in Public Law 2023,
445 chapter 412 that have not been expended may no longer be provided in supplemental
456 payments but may be used for the purposes of this legislation. The amendment also adds
467 an appropriations and allocations section.
